Spring cleaning routine 🌸 

My 3 spring cleaning tips: 

Make a Schedule - scope out your home: What areas need the most work? Where do you skip during routine cleaning? Those are the best places to start.
 
De-clutter - studies show that a disorganized home adds to your stress level. It signals to your brain that work isn’t done.

Take the hands-off approach with Dreame - arm yourself with a fully automated cleaning Dreamebot L10s Ultra by @dreame_tech, and you’ll enjoy a healthy, clean home all of spring season without all the extra work.

Tiny cuddles 🤍 It's not a secret but no one tells you that the hardest part about being a mom has little to do with your baby at all. It's the other aspects of your new title. Balancing your work, maintaining your relationships, navigating your hormones, operating on little sleep, plus keeping this little person safe all while trying to figure out who you are now after this new identity shift. Those are the hard parts. 

Managing yourself, this new you, that is the part that takes the work. I'm learning and evolving every day. When I say motherhood is hard, it is. Loving my baby and being her mom is not. That's the easy part.

Baked oats 🫶🏼🍓♥️

In a medium sized bowl add:
- 1 cup oats 
- 1 cup almond milk (or any milk)
- 1 tsp baking powder
- 1 tsp cinnamon 

Mix ingredients and pour in an oven safe dish
add dark chocolate chips and strawberries. 
Bake for 20 min at 350F 

(Optional) I like adding maple syrup and peanut butter on top.♥️
